    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>When deciding between buying a concealed camera or making your own, several factors need to be considered:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Technical expertise: Creating your own concealed camera requires some level of technical knowledge, including electronics, programming, and device integration. If you have the necessary skills or are willing to invest time in learning, making your own camera could be an option.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Cost: Buying a pre-existing concealed camera may be relatively more affordable compared to creating one from scratch. It would require purchasing individual components, tools, and possibly meeting minimum order quantities for certain parts.</p>
