he picture, then to himself, indicating that the girl is his sister.<br/><br/>Esther: “Oh, I see. That’s really nice. I bet she’s really proud of you.”<br/><br/>The Kid looks away, his expression unchanged.<br/><br/>Esther: “Hey, do you wanna play some video games? I just got a new one.”<br/><br/>Cut to an interior shot of Esther’s room. The Kid and Esther are sitting on the floor, playing a video game. Esther is kicking The Kid’s butt, and she’s giggling with joy.<br/><br/>Esther: “You’re no match for me! I’m the video game queen!”<br/><br/>The Kid looks at her, then reaches into his backpack and pulls out a pair of dice. He rolls them on the floor, and they land with a clatter.<br/><br/>Esther: “Oh, what’s this? You wanna play dice?”<br/><br/>The Kid nods, and they start playing. They laugh and chat, completely absorbed in the game.<br/><br/>Cut to a later shot of Esther’s room. It’s dark outside, and they’ve been playing for hours. The Kid is looking tired, and Esther notices.<br/><br/>Esther: “Hey, it’s getting late. Maybe you should head back to the orphanage.”<br/><br/>The Kid nods, and they get up to leave.<br/><br/>Esther: “Thanks for hanging out with me. I had a great time.”<br/><br/>The Kid hands Esther a small drawing, which she recognizes as a drawing of the two of them together. She smiles and thanks him.<br/><br/>Esther: “You’re a really great friend. I’m lucky to know you.”<br/><br/>The Kid nods, then begins to head out the door. As he’s leaving, Esther calls out to him.<br/><br/>Esther: “Hey, do you wanna come back tomorrow? We can hang out again.”<br/><br/>The Kid looks back at her, then nods and disappears down the hallway.<br/><br/>End of episode 2.</div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
