    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;">Provider com.fasterxml.aalto.stax.EventFactoryImpl not found when use android:sharedUserId</div><br/><br/>LLM response:<br/><div style="
    background-color: #fff3e6;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    padding: 10px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    border-radius: 5px;
    line-height: 1.6;"><p>This error occurs because when android:sharedUserId is used, the context of the application changes, and the EventFactoryImpl class is not found in this new context.</p>
<p>To resolve this issue, you can try the following solution:</p>
<ol>
<li>Add the following code to your app's build.gradle file:</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="language-gradle">android {
    // ...
    defaultConfig {
        // ...
        multiDexEnabled true
    }
    // ...
}
dependencies {
    // ...
    implementation 'com.android.support:multidex:1.0.3'
    // ...
}
</code></pre>
<ol>
<li>Add the following code to your Application class or create a new one if you haven't already:</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="language-java">public class MyApplication extends Application {

    @Override
    protected void attachBaseContext(Context base) {
        super.attachBaseContext(base);
        MultiDex.install(this);
    }
}
</code></pre>
<ol>
<li>Add the following code to your AndroidManifest.xml file within the application tag:</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="language-xml">&lt;application
    android:name=&quot;.MyApplication&quot;
    android:sharedUserId=&quot;com.example.sharedUserId&quot;
    //...
    &gt;
    //...
&lt;/application&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>Note: Replace com.example.sharedUserId with your own sharedUserId value.</p>
<p>This solution enables the use of multidex in your application, which solves the problem of class not found in the new application context.</p></div>

